race.comment: BAY OF THE SOUTH (6) won two trials and then led beaten 1L at the Gold Coast on debut. Was backed off the map and is sure to keep improving for the premier metro yard. Make strong appeal. NITE CHILL (8) brings narrow defeats at this level. Has to push over from a wide gate but presents fitter and will be right in the finish again. ZALIQUE (5) was heavily bet at Ipswich on debut but settled back and didn't finish it off. Has an awkward barrier but he's in good hands and Mallyon is a key jockey switch. ALL TOO FOXY (9) resumed at the Sunshine Coast and after settling forward stuck on to place distantly. Maps for the run of the race and he has more to give. RADIO WAVES (1) is a metro-trained improver drawn low.
